The paper discusses a problem related to DRAM refresh and proposes practical mechanisms to mitigate its performance overhead. This problem is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including computer architecture (cs.AR), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), systems and control (cs.SY), performance (cs.PF), and embedded systems (cs.ET). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
